<h2>The five laws</h2>

<p>The rules that keep it on-era. All five are machine-checkable and enforced in CI, a page
that breaks one does not ship.</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Palette.</strong> Only web-safe and classic named colors. Opaque UI.</li>
  <li><strong>Font.</strong> Only the nine era stacks, sizes only from the seven-step scale.</li>
  <li><strong>Shape.</strong> No rounded corners, no blurred shadows.</li>
  <li><strong>Motion.</strong> Linear or stepped easing only; everything honors reduced-motion.</li>
  <li><strong>Decency.</strong> No autoplay audio, no tracking, no surprise network calls.</li>
</ol>

